# Data Cleaning and Preparation Project

## About This Project

Data is only as valuable as its quality. Before any meaningful analysis can take place, datasets must be accurate, consistent, and reliable.

This project was completed as part of the Decodelab Data Analytics Internship and focuses on the critical process of data cleaning and preparation. The objective was to transform a raw dataset containing inconsistencies, duplicates, and missing values into a clean, structured dataset ready for analysis and decision-making.

This project demonstrates my ability to identify data quality issues, apply appropriate cleaning techniques, and prepare data for further analysis using industry best practices.

---

## Project Objective

The goal of this project was to improve data quality and ensure the dataset was suitable for analysis by:

* Identifying and removing duplicate records.
* Handling missing and blank values.
* Correcting inconsistencies in the dataset.
* Standardizing data formats.
* Improving overall data accuracy and reliability.

---

## Tools Used

* Microsoft Excel
* Power Query
* Data Validation Techniques

---

## Data Cleaning Process

The following steps were carried out during the cleaning process:

### Data Assessment

Reviewed the dataset to identify quality issues and understand the structure of the data.

### Handling Missing Values

Examined blank and null values and applied appropriate cleaning techniques where necessary.

### Removing Duplicates

Identified and removed duplicate records to ensure data integrity.

### Standardization

Standardize formats across columns to improve consistency and usability.

### Data Validation

Performed checks to confirm the dataset was accurate, complete, and ready for analysis.

---

## Key Outcomes

Through this project:

* Data quality was significantly improved.
* Duplicate records were eliminated.
* Inconsistencies were corrected.
* The dataset became analysis-ready.
* Reporting accuracy and reliability were enhanced.

---

## Why Data Cleaning Matters

Data cleaning is one of the most important stages of the analytics process. Poor-quality data can lead to inaccurate insights and poor business decisions.

This project reinforced the importance of building a strong analytical foundation before proceeding to exploratory analysis, reporting, or dashboard development.

